{
  "texts": [
    "Materials and methodsThe study uses two gold standard corpora available in the literature for phenotype concept recognition: (i) a corpus of 228 scientific abstracts collected from PubMed, initially annotated and published by Groza et al. [22], and subsequently refined by Lobo et al.",
    "[23] (named HPO-GS from here on); and (ii) the dev component of the corpus made available through Track 3 of BioCreative VIII (454 entries), focusing on extraction and normalization of phenotypes resulting from genetic diseases, based on dysmorphology physical examination [24] (named BIOC-GS from here on).",
    "An example of an entry is: \"ABDOMEN: Small umbilical hernia.",
    "Mild distention.",
    "\"All experiments were conducted using these two corpora."
  ]
}